Hi Josh!

=20

Good morning and thank you for sharing your thoughts! Yes, if you are =
considering Berlin, housing is the aspect to be prepared for (duck - =
cover - hold on to) =E2=80=93 the real estate market has been going =
crazy for the last 15 years (maybe not compared to NYc standards?!), =
affordable housing for small incomes can only be found in the periphery, =
that is an hour or two away by subway/train from the center. I know that =
this does not sound intimidating to an American ear, but it tends to be =
rather rural out there with not as much intercultural competence among =
the native population as you might expect =E2=80=93 plus, I see you =
looking for a place in the *center* of things, right?!

=20

Now, that I come to think about it, I have another author and co-worker =
that I might want to recommend making contact with once you have a more =
detailed  vision of your future: Cecile Rossant is a writer and =
wonderful person who is originally from NYC, but has been living in =
Berlin for quite a while (mid 90s?!). She is partly of French decent as =
well - https://de-de.facebook.com/cecile.rossant

As I said: a wonderful and interesting person.

=20

So, you please keep popping up in my inbox! Much appreciated!

=20

And, yes, it would be wonderful to have a chat with you =E2=80=93 can I =
ask for another week or so, before we make it happen? We are right in =
the =E2=80=9Eend-of-the-school year=E2=80=9C-period, quite stressful =
=E2=80=A6 Let=E2=80=99s look into late July/early August, how about =
that?!

=20

Good thoughts

J=C3=B6rg

=20

