=20

Firstly, congratulations!!! It looks like you're in an amazingly =
beautiful space, and such a wonderful family. Josephine is so big now!!

=20

Secondly, I cannot thank you enough for your kind offer reg. Berlin. =
Right now we're very much in the air, with big questions about my work, =
my startup, the boys' school in NYC, the rate of infection, etc. etc. =
etc. all TBD. That said, please be ready for me to reappear in your =
inbox with a request for introductions - I'm quite keen to explore =
living in Berlin and as I understand it the housing component is perhaps =
the most complicated element.=20

=20

Regardless of all of the above let me know if you have time in the weeks =
ahead for a quick zoom just to catch up. On a purely personal level one =
of the biggest gifts of the pandemic is a reaffirmation of our intention =
to stay well connected with true friends, and I'd be keen to hear from =
you directly about how you got through these crazy last few months!

=20

With gratitude,

Josh

=20

P.S. I would be remiss not to answer Josephine's question (and thanks to =
her for asking!) The cats are being taken care of by a friend who is =
staying at our apartment until September. At that point we're likely to =
send them to live with my sister, who just bought a nice big house in =
Seattle, for their retirement.=20

=20


